Rwanda has increased its women representation in Parliament, beating its current world record of 64 percent. According to Taarifa News the new world record for women representation in parliament has shot up to 67.5 percent. Out of a total parliamentary membership of 80, women occupy 54 seats. The United Nations and the Inter-Parliamentary Union demand a 30 percent minimum threshold for women representation. Ghana has 36 women in Parliament and this represents 12.75 percent. To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
    supports HTML5 video This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window. The new record came to light last Tuesday night after the National Electoral Commission announced the September 3 parliamentary elections results.